#!/bin/bash
langf=$(tput bold && tput setaf 4)
langn=powershell
langv=$(pwsh --version)

g=$(tput setaf 5)
b=$(tput bold)
reset=$(tput sgr0)

cat << EndOfIntro

${g}glasnt${reset}'s wat-reference for ${langf}${langn}${reset}

We're using: 
${langv}

Try these examples: 

if (36 > 42) { "true" } else { "false" }

if (36 < 42) { "true" } else { "false" }

See the ${b}${langn}/README.md${reset} for references, and more information. 
ðŸ”ŒðŸš
EndOfIntro
